{
 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 VideoTutorialPage\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 Escalated perspectives confirmed\n\nFrom the a11y-critic hand-off:\n\n- **Auditory Access \u2014 HIGH** \u2192 deep review\n- **Screen Reader & Semantic Structure \u2014 MEDIUM** \u2192 deep review\n\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Keyboard & Motor Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent.\n\nOnly the two escalated checklists are run below.\n\n---\n\n## Step 4 \u2014 Per-perspective checklists\n\n### Perspective 4 \u2014 Auditory Access (HIGH)\n\nWCAG (AA): 1.2.1, 1.2.2, 1.2.3, 1.2.5, 1.4.2\n\n**Code-level checklist:**\n\n| # | Checklist item | WCAG | Result |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Every `<video>` with speech has `<track kind=\"captions\">` with valid `src` | 1.2.2 | **FINDING A1** \u2014 no `<track>` of any kind on the `<video>` |\n| 2 | Every `<audio>` has adjacent transcript/link | 1.2.1 | N/A \u2014 no `<audio>` element; content is synchronized media, so 1.2.1 (audio-only/video-only) does not govern here |\n| 3 | Player controls (play, pause, volume, caption toggle) keyboard-operable | 2.1.1 | **PARTIAL** \u2014 play/pause, seek, mute, volume are native `<button>`/`<input type=\"range\">` and keyboard-operable (PASS); caption toggle is absent \u2192 **FINDING A2** |\n| 4 | Visual indicators accompany all auditory alerts/notifications | 1.1.1 | **FINDING A5** \u2014 completion (880 Hz) and error (220 Hz) beeps have no visual counterpart |\n| 5 | No audio auto-plays, or auto-play has immediate pause within first focusable element | 1.4.2 | **PASS** \u2014 `isPlaying` initializes `false`; `video.play()` fires only on user activation; no `autoplay` attribute |\n\n**Content-level checklist (human verification):**\n\n| # | Checklist item | WCAG | Result |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 6 | Caption accuracy and timing | 1.2.2 | **Moot / superseded** \u2014 captions are entirely absent (see A1); nothing to verify until they exist |\n| 7 | Transcript includes speaker identification | \u2014 | **Moot** \u2014 no transcript exists (see A4) |\n| 8 | Audio descriptions cover visual-only information | 1.2.3, 1.2.5 | **FINDING A3 / A4** \u2014 no descriptions track and no text alternative; coverage of visual-only content needs author verification once infrastructure exists |\n\n**Red flags:**\n- `<video>` with speech and no `<track>` element \u2192 **FIRES \u2192 auto-CRITICAL** (A1)\n- Media player with no keyboard controls \u2192 does not fire (controls are operable)\n- Audio auto-plays with no visible stop control \u2192 does not fire (no autoplay)\n\n**Correctly-implemented items acknowledged (not findings):** play/pause `aria-label` updates on state change; seek bar carries `aria-valuetext` with human-readable positions; mute `aria-label` reflects current state; controls wrapped in `role=\"group\"` with `aria-label=\"Video controls\"`. These are genuine positives \u2014 flagging them would be false-alarm noise.\n\n---\n\n### Perspective 6 \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n\nWCAG (AA): 1.1.1, 1.3.1, 1.3.2, 2.4.2, 2.4.4, 2.4.6, 3.1.1, 3.1.2, 3.3.1, 3.3.2, 4.1.2, 4.1.3\n\n| # | Checklist item | WCAG | Result |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Landmark regions present and correct | 1.3.1 | **PASS** \u2014 `<main className=\"tutorial-page\">` present; `<section>` groups the meta block under an `<h2>` |\n| 2 | Heading hierarchy logical, `<h1>` present, no skipped levels | 2.4.6 | **PASS** \u2014 `<h1>{title}</h1>` \u2192 `<h2>About this tutorial</h2>`. (Descriptiveness of `{title}` depends on the prop value \u2014 content verification.) |\n| 3 | Informative images have descriptive `alt`; decorative `alt=\"\"` | 1.1.1 | **N/A** \u2014 no `<img>` elements; control glyphs (\u25b6 \u23f8 \ud83d\udd0a \ud83d\udd07) sit inside buttons whose `aria-label` supplies the accessible name |\n| 4 | DOM/source order matches visual reading order | 1.3.2 | **PASS** \u2014 source order (h1 \u2192 video \u2192 controls \u2192 meta) matches reading order |\n| 5 | Unique, descriptive `<title>` | 2.4.2 | **N/A (out of component scope)** \u2014 document `<title>` lives in `<head>`; verify at page level |\n| 6 | Link text describes destination | 2.4.4 | **N/A** \u2014 no links present (the missing transcript link is tracked under A4, not here) |\n| 7 | `lang` on `<html>` | 3.1.1 | **N/A (out of component scope)** \u2014 `<html lang>` not controllable from this fixture; verify at page level |\n| 8 | Foreign-language phrases wrapped in `lang` | 3.1.2 | **N/A** \u2014 no foreign-language content |\n| 9 | Every form input has a label with programmatic association | 3.3.2 | **PASS** \u2014 both `<input type=\"range\">` carry `aria-label` (\"Seek\", \"Volume\"); a visible `<label>` element is absent but the aria-label + adjacent icon/time context is standard, acceptable media-player practice |\n| 10 | Error messages identify field and associate via `aria-describedby` | 3.3.1 | **N/A** \u2014 no form-validation inputs; the video load error is a status message, handled under 4.1.3 |\n| 11 | Custom widgets use correct ARIA roles matching APG | 4.1.2 | **PASS with FINDING S2** \u2014 native elements carry correct implicit roles (button, slider); the `<video>` `aria-label=\"video player\"` is generic and does not describe the content \u2192 S2 |\n| 12 | Status messages use `aria-live` with appropriate urgency | 4.1.3 | **FINDING S1** \u2014 `hasCompleted` and `hasError` set state but render nothing to the DOM; no live region exists |\n| 13 | SPA route changes managed | \u2014 | **N/A** \u2014 single component, no routing |\n\n**Red flags:**\n- No `<main>` landmark \u2192 does not fire (`<main>` present)\n- Form inputs without any label \u2192 does not fire (all labeled)\n- Custom widget with no ARIA role \u2192 does not fire (native roles + `role=\"group\"`)\n- Missing `lang` on `<html>` \u2192 out of component scope; cannot confirm from this fixture\n\nNo Screen Reader red flag fires \u2192 **no auto-CRITICAL** from this perspective.\n\n**Correctly-implemented item acknowledged (not a finding):** `<span className=\"time-display\" aria-live=\"off\">`. Setting the elapsed-time readout to `aria-live=\"off\"` is the **right** decision \u2014 a per-second live announcement would flood the user with noise. This is good calibration, not a defect.\n\n---\n\n## Step 5 \u2014 Findings\n\n**Finding A1:** The tutorial `<video>` carries speech throughout (instructor narration) but has no `<track kind=\"captions\">`. A Deaf or hard-of-hearing user receives none of the spoken instruction \u2014 the primary content of the page is entirely inaccessible to them.\n**WCAG:** 1.2.2 Captions (Prerecorded) \u2014 Level A\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** CRITICAL (red flag: video with speech, no track)\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `<video ref={videoRef} src={videoSrc} aria-label=\"video player\" className=\"tutorial-video\" />` \u2014 fixture lines ~114\u2013119. No child `<track>` element of any kind.\n**Fix:** Author a synchronized caption file (WebVTT) covering all narration and meaningful non-speech audio; add `<track kind=\"captions\" src=\"\u2026\" srclang=\"en\" label=\"English\" default />`. Pair with the caption control in A2.\n\n---\n\n**Finding A2:** The player exposes play/pause, seek, mute, and volume, but no control to toggle captions on/off. Even once a caption track exists, the user has no way to turn it on.\n**WCAG:** 1.2.2 Captions (Prerecorded) \u2014 Level A (user control over captions)\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** MINOR (subordinate to A1 \u2014 moot until captions exist, but must ship alongside them)\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `.player-controls` group (fixture lines ~121\u2013170) ends after the volume slider; comment at ~line 169 confirms the omission.\n**Fix:** Add a keyboard-operable caption toggle button with `aria-pressed` reflecting state, wired to `videoRef.current.textTracks[0].mode`.\n\n---\n\n**Finding A3:** No `<track kind=\"descriptions\">` is present. If the tutorial conveys any information visually that is not spoken (on-screen text, UI being demonstrated, pointer movement), a blind user misses it entirely.\n**WCAG:** 1.2.5 Audio Description (Prerecorded) \u2014 Level AA (also 1.2.3, Level A)\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `<video>` element (fixture lines ~114\u2013119) has no descriptions track; comment at ~line 113 confirms.\n**Fix:** Produce audio description covering visual-only content and add a descriptions track (or an extended-description alternative). Note: a text transcript (A4) satisfies 1.2.3 (Level A) but does **not** discharge 1.2.5 (Level AA) \u2014 actual audio description is required for AA. `[Human verification required \u2014 whether visual-only information exists, and its coverage, cannot be confirmed from source]`\n\n---\n\n**Finding A4:** No transcript section and no link to a transcript. A transcript is the media alternative that satisfies 1.2.3 and is the primary fallback for users who cannot use captions or audio at all (e.g., deaf-blind users on a braille display).\n**WCAG:** 1.2.3 Media Alternative for Prerecorded \u2014 Level A\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** Comment at fixture lines ~173\u2013174; the only content below the player is `<section className=\"tutorial-meta\">` with a duration line \u2014 no transcript markup or link. (Note: the fixture comment cites 1.2.1, but 1.2.1 governs audio-only/video-only content; for this synchronized media the correct citation is 1.2.3.)\n**Fix:** Provide a full text transcript (speaker identification, dialogue, and description of visual-only actions) in an adjacent `<section>` or as a clearly labeled link near the player. `[Human verification required \u2014 transcript completeness and speaker identification cannot be confirmed from source]`\n\n---\n\n**Finding A5:** Video completion and load-error are signalled **only** by a generated tone (880 Hz on `ended`, 220 Hz sawtooth on `error`). `hasCompleted` and `hasError` are stored in state but never rendered. A Deaf or hard-of-hearing user \u2014 and in fact any user with sound off \u2014 gets no indication that the video finished or that it failed to load.\n**WCAG:** 1.1.1 Non-text Content \u2014 Level A (a sound conveying information requires an equivalent text/visual alternative)\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR (driven by the silent error state \u2014 the user cannot tell a broken video from a slow one)\n**Route to:** UX Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `handleEnded` (fixture lines ~34\u201344) and `handleError` (lines ~45\u201355) each build an `AudioContext` oscillator and emit a beep; the returned JSX (lines ~106\u2013181) contains no conditional rendering keyed on `hasCompleted` or `hasError`.\n**Fix:** Render a visible status for both states (e.g., a completion confirmation and an error message with retry). This is the same DOM change that resolves S1 \u2014 implement once, satisfying both the visual-indicator (A5) and the announced-status (S1) requirements.\n\n---\n\n**Finding S1:** `hasCompleted` and `hasError` change React state but produce no DOM output and no `aria-live` region, so assistive technology announces nothing. A screen reader user who triggers the video and walks away has no way to know it completed; on error they receive no announcement and are left waiting indefinitely.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.3 Status Messages \u2014 Level AA\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** `setHasCompleted(true)` (line ~36) and `setHasError(true)` (line ~46) with no corresponding render; no element in the JSX carries `role=\"status\"`, `role=\"alert\"`, or `aria-live` for these states. (The `time-display` uses `aria-live=\"off\"`, which is correct and unrelated.)\n**Fix:** Render completion into a `role=\"status\"` / `aria-live=\"polite\"` region and the load error into a `role=\"alert\"` region. Wording should be human-readable (\"Tutorial complete.\" / \"Video failed to load. Retry.\"). Converges with A5's fix.\n\n---\n\n**Finding S2:** The `<video>` element's accessible name is the generic `aria-label=\"video player\"`, which tells a screen reader user the element type but nothing about the content. It duplicates what the role already conveys and wastes the naming opportunity.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value \u2014 Level A (name quality)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MINOR (the video is still identifiable and the `<h1>` supplies page context \u2014 workaround exists)\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `aria-label=\"video player\"` \u2014 fixture line ~117; comment at ~line 111 confirms intent.\n**Fix:** Set the accessible name to describe the specific tutorial, e.g., `aria-label={`Tutorial video: ${title}`}` or reference the `<h1>` via `aria-labelledby`. `[Human verification required \u2014 ideal descriptive wording is a content decision]`\n\n---\n\n## Contract blocks \u2014 new CRITICAL / MAJOR findings\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: auditory-no-captions-track\nfingerprint: 7f3c2b9d4e6a0155\nsource: perspective-audit Auditory Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.2.2 Captions (Prerecorded)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 A/AA; 1.2.2 is in scope (Level A)\nperspective_alarms: auditory_access=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: `<video>` element (fixture lines ~114\u2013119) has no `<track>` child; expected behavior states narration runs throughout\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 inspect the `<video>` element for a captions track\nexpected_behavior: Deaf/HoH user reads synchronized captions of all narration\nactual_behavior: no captions rendered; spoken content is entirely inaccessible\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: auditory-no-audio-description\nfingerprint: 3e91a7c4d20b6f88\nsource: perspective-audit Auditory Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.2.5 Audio Description (Prerecorded); also 1.2.3\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 / WCAG 2.0 AA \u2014 1.2.5 in scope\nperspective_alarms: auditory_access=HIGH\nevidence: no `<track kind=\"descriptions\">` on `<video>` (fixture lines ~114\u2013119); comment line ~113\nreproduction_steps: source review only; coverage of visual-only content needs content-author verification\nexpected_behavior: blind user receives audio description of visual-only information\nactual_behavior: no description track or extended-description alternative present\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: auditory-no-transcript-alternative\nfingerprint: b2d5e8017a4c9f36\nsource: perspective-audit Auditory Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.2.3 Media Alternative for Prerecorded\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 / WCAG 2.0 A \u2014 1.2.3 in scope\nperspective_alarms: auditory_access=HIGH\nevidence: no transcript markup or link below player (fixture lines ~173\u2013179); only a duration line renders\nreproduction_steps: source review only; transcript completeness needs content-author verification\nexpected_behavior: transcript with speaker ID and visual-action description available adjacent to the player\nactual_behavior: no transcript or link exists\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: auditory-audio-only-status\nfingerprint: 5c1f9a3e7b8d0244\nsource: perspective-audit Auditory Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.1.1 Non-text Content\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 / WCAG 2.0 A \u2014 1.1.1 in scope\nperspective_alarms: auditory_access=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: `handleEnded` (lines ~34\u201344) and `handleError` (lines ~45\u201355) emit oscillator beeps; no JSX renders `hasCompleted`/`hasError`\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 trace `hasCompleted`/`hasError` to render output (none)\nexpected_behavior: completion and error are shown visually (and announced) in addition to any sound\nactual_behavior: status conveyed by tone alone; no visual indicator for a Deaf/HoH or sound-off user\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: sr-status-not-exposed\nfingerprint: 9a4c7e2f158b3d60\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 4.1.3 Status Messages\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 / WCAG 2.0 AA \u2014 4.1.3 is a WCAG 2.1 addition; in scope where WCAG 2.1/2.2 applies\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM, auditory_access=HIGH\nevidence: `setHasCompleted`/`setHasError` (lines ~36, ~46) with no `role=\"status\"`, `role=\"alert\"`, or `aria-live` region in JSX\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 inspect JSX for a live region tied to completion/error state\nexpected_behavior: screen reader announces completion (polite) and error (assertive) without a focus move\nactual_behavior: no DOM change and no live region; AT announces nothing\ntrend: new\n\n---\n\n## Step 6 \u2014 Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** VideoTutorialPage (custom React video tutorial player)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Auditory Access (HIGH), Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Keyboard & Motor Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 1 |\n| MAJOR | 4 |\n| MINOR | 2 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 0 |\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\nNone. Both escalated perspectives produced findings. (Auditory Access carries the CRITICAL; Screen Reader carries one MAJOR + one MINOR.)\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- Status messages not exposed to AT (no `aria-live`) \u2014 Screen Reader \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.3 (S1)\n- No caption toggle control \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.2.2 (A2)\n\n**Visual Design**\n- (none)\n\n**UX Design**\n- Completion/error signalled by audio only, no visual indicator \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.1.1 (A5)\n\n**Content Author**\n- No captions track on speech video \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.2.2 (A1)\n- No audio description track \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.2.5 (A3)\n- No transcript / media alternative \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.2.3 (A4)\n- Generic `aria-label=\"video player\"` on the video \u2014 Screen Reader \u2014 MINOR \u2014 4.1.2 (S2)\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n- **Audio description coverage (A3):** whether the tutorial contains visual-only information requiring description, and whether description is complete \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source.\n- **Transcript completeness (A4):** transcript accuracy, speaker identification, and inclusion of visual actions \u2014 content-author verification once a transcript exists.\n- **Caption accuracy (A1):** once a caption track is authored, timing and accuracy need verification (currently moot \u2014 no captions exist).\n- **Descriptive video name wording (S2):** the ideal accessible-name text is a content decision.\n- **Page-level context out of component scope:** document `<title>` (2.4.2) and `<html lang>` (3.1.1) are not present in this fixture and must be verified at the page that hosts this component.\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**BLOCK** \u2014 A CRITICAL finding is present (A1: speech video with no captions), which alone blocks all Deaf and hard-of-hearing users from the page's primary content. Four MAJOR findings compound the barrier across both Deaf/HoH and blind users. Do not ship until at minimum A1 is resolved; A3, A4, A5, and S1 should be fixed in the same cycle, since A5 and S1 share a single DOM-rendering fix.\n",
